how csm works after hand is over the cards just used are placed back into the shuffler to be mixed with the other cards in the shoe shuffle master king uses an elevator system to randomize the cards as the elevator is moved up and down cards are randomly inserted into one of the shelves in the elevator the shuffler randomly selects shelf of cards to deliver into the shoe because of the non-linear process every discard re-inserted following hand has chance of appearing in the next round although shuffle master says the king differs from their competitors continuous shufflers because the others use linear design most csms so the same thing they put the discards back into play and does away with the dealers having to stop to physically shuffle the cards at the end of shoe the house edge the continuous shufflers have no benefits for the player and has been dubbed the uncomfortable shoes it eliminates card counting for the skilled player and will also have major disadvantage for the basic strategy player it speeds up the game when the csm was first introduced many players felt it would probably increase the house edge as it turns out this is not entirely true michael shackleford the wizard of odds did mathematical analysis of the continuous shuffling machines and found that there was very slight reduction in the house edge in four deck game the edge is percent and in an eight deck game is tis percent before you get excited about slight reduction in the house edge you have to realize that when the casino uses csm the speed of the games is increased by about percent the basic strategy player stands to lose more in the long run because they are exposing more money to the house edge as player feel it treat to visit casino that offers double and single deck games would hate to see these games eliminated altogether even multi deck shoe game is preferable to the continuous shuffling machines the best way you can let the casinos know this is by refusing to play
